abstract: Attorney Michael Avenatti should be prevented from practicing law for pocketing a client's settlement and covering his tracks through “deceit, dishonesty and lies,” a lawyer for the California State Bar said Wednesday.
snippet: Attorney Michael Avenatti should be prevented from practicing law for pocketing a client's settlement and covering his tracks through “deceit, dishonesty and lies,” a lawyer for the California State Bar said Wednesday.
lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — Attorney Michael Avenatti should be prevented from practicing law for pocketing a client's settlement and covering his tracks through “deceit, dishonesty and lies,” a lawyer for the California State Bar said Wednesday.
headline_main: California Bar: Avenatti Stole From Client Using ‘Deceit’
headline_print_headline: California Bar: Avenatti Stole From Client Using ‘Deceit’

abstract: A citizenship law helps non-Muslim refugees from Muslim-majority countries but ignores Muslim refugees from other nations.
snippet: A citizenship law helps non-Muslim refugees from Muslim-majority countries but ignores Muslim refugees from other nations.
lead_paragraph: On the face of it, India’s new citizenship law might seem quite reasonable in its offer of expedited citizenship for migrants of minority religions from neighboring countries. What’s not to like in offering refuge to minority groups facing repression in predominantly Muslim states?

abstract: A Wisconsin appeals court on Wednesday denied a request from the state Justice Department to immediately put on hold a judge's ruling to purge  more than 200,000 voter registrations in the key swing state before it hears from the other side.
snippet: A Wisconsin appeals court on Wednesday denied a request from the state Justice Department to immediately put on hold a judge's ruling to purge  more than 200,000 voter registrations in the key swing state before it hears from the other side.
lead_paragraph: MADISON, Wis. — A Wisconsin appeals court on Wednesday denied a request from the state Justice Department to immediately put on hold a judge's ruling to purge more than 200,000 voter registrations in the key swing state before it hears from the other side.
headline_main: Wisconsin Appeals Court Delays Ruling on Voter Purge Case
headline_print_headline: Wisconsin Appeals Court Delays Ruling on Voter Purge Case

abstract: A winnowed field of Democratic presidential contenders takes the debate stage Thursday for a sixth and final time in 2019, as candidates seek to convince anxious voters that they are the party's best hope to deny President Donald Trump a second term.
snippet: A winnowed field of Democratic presidential contenders takes the debate stage Thursday for a sixth and final time in 2019, as candidates seek to convince anxious voters that they are the party's best hope to deny President Donald Trump a second te...
lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — A winnowed field of Democratic presidential contenders takes the debate stage Thursday for a sixth and final time in 2019, as candidates seek to convince anxious voters that they are the party's best hope to deny President Donald Trump a second term.
headline_main: 2020 Democrats Prepare to Debate in Shadow of Impeachment

abstract: Cuba’s government accused the Trump administration on Wednesday of orchestrating the end of the island's medical missions to several Latin American countries in order to cut one of the country's main revenue sources.
snippet: Cuba’s government accused the Trump administration on Wednesday of orchestrating the end of the island's medical missions to several Latin American countries in order to cut one of the country's main revenue sources.
lead_paragraph: HAVANA — Cuba’s government accused the Trump administration on Wednesday of orchestrating the end of the island's medical missions to several Latin American countries in order to cut one of the country's main revenue sources.
headline_main: Cuba Blasts US Over End of Medical Missions in Some Nations
headline_print_headline: Cuba Blasts US Over End of Medical Missions in Some Nations

abstract: As U.S. President Donald Trump on Wednesday appeared on the brink of becoming only the third U.S. president ever to be impeached, history suggests investors need not worry, even though it adds uncertainty on Wall Street.
snippet: As U.S. President Donald Trump on Wednesday appeared on the brink of becoming only the third U.S. president ever to be impeached, history suggests investors need not worry, even though it adds uncertainty on Wall Street.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - As U.S. President Donald Trump on Wednesday appeared on the brink of becoming only the third U.S. president ever to be impeached, history suggests investors need not worry, even though it adds uncertainty on Wall Street.
headline_main: Trump Impeachment? History Suggests Wall Street Need Not Worry
headline_print_headline: Trump Impeachment? History Suggests Wall Street Need Not Worry

abstract: Two U.S. Republican lawmakers on Wednesday opposed the impeachment of President Donald Trump with remarks that alluded to the Biblical account of the crucifixion of Jesus Christ, causing the phrase "Trump to Jesus" to trend on Twitter.
snippet: Two U.S. Republican lawmakers on Wednesday opposed the impeachment of President Donald Trump with remarks that alluded to the Biblical account of the crucifixion of Jesus Christ, causing the phrase "Trump to Jesus" to trend on Twitter.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Two U.S. Republican lawmakers on Wednesday opposed the impeachment of President Donald Trump with remarks that alluded to the Biblical account of the crucifixion of Jesus Christ, causing the phrase "Trump to Jesus" to trend on Twitter.
headline_main: Republican Lawmakers, Opposing Trump Impeachment, Cite Crucifixion of Jesus
headline_print_headline: Republican Lawmakers, Opposing Trump Impeachment, Cite Crucifixion of Jesus

abstract: The move would prevent migrants convicted of misdemeanors like possessing a fake ID from receiving asylum.
snippet: The move would prevent migrants convicted of misdemeanors like possessing a fake ID from receiving asylum.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Trump administration moved on Wednesday to bar immigrants convicted of minor crimes in the United States from obtaining asylum, the latest effort to limit protections extended to those fleeing persecution.
